news.title: Mumbai: EOW arrests five developers for cheating buyers in three separate cases
news.para: The city Economic Offences Wing (EOW) arrested five developers in three separate cheating cases involving around Rs 28 crore over the last 24 hours. All the arrested developers have been sent to police custody.

news.title: Chennai Corporation issues 704 stop-work notices for building violation
news.para: Cracking down on violators, the Greater Chennai Corporation has issued 704 stop-work notices for under-construction buildings where officials found deviations from original plans.

news.title: South Indian Bank raises MCLR rates by up to 0.20%
news.para: The Marginal Cost of Funds Based Lending Rates (MCLR) applicable for multiple tenors has been revised with effect from June 20, 2022, South Indian Bank said in regulatory filing on Saturday.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body plans single property, water tax recovery notice
news.para: Not only this, even payment will be recovered at one counter so that people could clear their dues in one go instead of knocking at two doors. At the moment for both types of recoveries, the defaulters get separate notices.

news.title: Maharashtra: 403 developers use e-registration facility from offices, 95 more apply
news.para: While two months ago, 347 developers’ applications were approved, another 56 have been recently given a nod, said state officials.

news.title: Transfer of encroached properties not allowed: Chandigarh Housing Board
news.para: In such cases, the applicants are required to remove the encroachments prior to initiating transfer mutation/execution of lease deed or conveyance deed, said Garg.

news.title: Seven malls owe Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike Rs 46 crore property tax
news.para: According to data shared by the Palike’s revenue section, Mantri Square is the biggest defaulter with dues of Rs 27 crore. The mall has not paid tax since 2019.

news.title: Gurugram: IIT Delhi experts, audit firm's team inspect Chintels Paradiso tower
news.para: Two people had died in the vertical collapse of a portion of flats from the sixth to second floors of the residential society on February 9. The collapse occurred in Tower D of the society, which has several towers with 18 floors each.

news.title: Mumbai: Liberty Horizon' builder to pay buyer refund, rental loss, interest costs
news.para: According to the complaint, home buyer Mahesh Pistolwala purchased a flat measuring 363 square feet at the Liberty Horizon project at Kothimbe village in Karjat Taluka for a consideration of Rs 6,50,000 in 2013.

news.title: Ghatkopar: 12 years on, no homes; 12 FIRs against Shraddha Skyline builder
news.para: Normally police clubs all the FIRs but on city police commissioner’s instructions, the Pant Nagar police have filed 12 separate FIRs with common complaints.

news.title: RLDA invites bids to lease out 60,407 sq metre of land at Dhanbad
news.para: ​The total land area is 81,788 sqm, of which 60,407 sqm will be leased out for residential development for 99 years. The balance area of 21,381 sqm will be utilised for redevelopment of existing railway quarters, the release said.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: EOW arrests builder for duping home buyers
news.para: According to the EOW, Sarangi was associated with Basera Designs Pvt Limited, a real estate company, which had announced to float a housing project in Sijua area on the city outskirts in 2016.

news.title: Delhi: Why it is likely to be another monsoon of opportunity lost
news.para: However, residents allege that rainwater won’t be tapped even this monsoon due to unresolved queries and the lackadaisical attitude of the authorities.

news.title: Goa: GIDC gives nod for third e-auction of 'SEZ land'
news.para: Half the plots that were put up for auction during the second round of the e-auction had no takers, prompting GIDC to go for the third round.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board demolishes four illegal structures in Ram Darbar
news.para: CHB is now computing the demolition cost to be recovered from the allottees and in case of its non-payment their allotments may be cancelled, he added.
